{
  "texts": [
    "The solid lines are the mean rates, and the shaded areas signify standard deviations of the models.",
    "This visualization points out the comparison of learning curve of various algorithms and thus can be used for evaluating their generalization ability.",
    "For example, a thin area under the curve of shading and virtually negligible difference between the training line and testing imply that the model feature is well trained and does not over-train the model.",
    "On the other hand, larger-divergence values refer to greater variance that may be asserting some problems such as overfitting or underfitting problems.",
    "This figure guides the selection of how the various models learn and adapt in the given dataset to ensure that the right model is used for the particular task."
  ]
}